# Integration Test Log — issue-41-prompt-reminders
# Date: 2026-03-08
# Environment: Mock signal server (port 9090), worktree bot with feature branch

## Test 1: Basic Mention Smoke Test
- Message: "claude: say hello back in one word"
- Expected: Bot processes mention, invokes LLM, sends response
- Actual: Bot received message, spawned claude -p, got response in 42.3s, delivered via fallback
- Result: PASS

## Test 2: Simple Mode Reminder (Default)
- Message: "claude: set a reminder for 30 seconds from now saying test simple reminder"
- Expected: Bot calls set_reminder with mode "simple" (or default), reminder fires as text message
- Actual: Bot called set_reminder with {"reminderText":"test simple reminder","dueAt":1772888898782,"mode":"simple"}
  - Reminder #1 created, mode=simple
  - Scheduler fired reminder ~17s after dueAt, marked as sent
  - No Claude session spawned (correct for simple mode)
- Database: id=1, status=sent, mode=simple, sentAt=1772888916070
- Result: PASS

## Test 3: Prompt Mode Reminder (Core New Feature)
- Message: "claude: set a reminder for 30 seconds from now in prompt mode saying check the current time and report it"
- Expected: Bot calls set_reminder with mode "prompt", reminder spawns Claude session when it fires
- Actual: Bot called set_reminder with {"reminderText":"check the current time and report it","dueAt":1772889056134,"mode":"prompt"}
  - Reminder #2 created, mode=prompt
  - Scheduler detected prompt mode, delegated to recurring executor
  - Log: "recurring: executing reminder #2: check the current time and report it"
  - Log: "recurring: reminder #2 completed (via MCP)"
  - Claude session spawned with MCP tools, executed successfully
- Database: id=2, status=sent, mode=prompt, sentAt=1772889098124
- Result: PASS

## Test 4: Set Both Modes + List Reminders
- Message: "claude: set two reminders - one simple reminder for 1 hour from now saying check dishes, and one prompt mode reminder for 1 hour from now saying check the weather forecast. Then list all my reminders."
- Expected: Both modes accepted, list_reminders shows [prompt] label for prompt mode
- Actual: Bot called:
  - set_reminder {"reminderText":"check dishes","dueAt":1772892828222,"mode":"simple"}
  - set_reminder {"reminderText":"check the weather forecast","dueAt":1772892828222,"mode":"prompt"}
  - list_reminders {} — displayed both reminders
- Database:
  - id=3: mode=simple, status=pending (not yet due)
  - id=4: mode=prompt, status=pending (not yet due)
- Result: PASS

## Summary
- All 4 tests passed
- Simple mode reminders work exactly as before (backward compatible)
- Prompt mode reminders correctly spawn Claude sessions via the recurring executor
- The set_reminder MCP tool correctly accepts and stores the mode parameter
- The list_reminders MCP tool correctly displays reminders with mode info
- Database schema correctly stores mode column with "simple" default

